text:
="preserve">Hurricane Iota was an Atlantic tropical cyclone which formed in November 2020. The hurricane affected Nicaragua and Honduras in Central America.
Iota was the first time a 30th named storm had ever developed in the Atlantic Basin.
The storm was the second strongest hurricane in the month of November. It was the first Category 5 hurricane in the 2020 Atlantic hurricane season. The storm did $1.4 billion in damage and killed 61 people.
